cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Felections%2Flok-sabha-election%2Flok-sabha-elections-2024-exit-polls-today-key-seats-to-watch-out-for-for-124060100196_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Felections%2Flok-sabha-election%2Flok-sabha-elections-2024-exit-polls-today-key-seats-to-watch-out-for-for-124060100196_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20AI%20Is%20Cracking%20A%20Hard%20Problem%20-%20Giving%20Computers%20A%20Sense%20Of%20Smell%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOver%20100%20years%20ago%2C%20Alexander%20Graham%20Bell%20asked%20the%20readers%20of%20National%20Geographic%20to%20do%20something%20bold%20and%20fresh%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fhdl.loc.gov%2Floc.mss%2Fmagbell.37500401%5C%22%3Eto%20found%20a%20new%20science%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20sciences%20based%20on%20the%20measurements%20of%20sound%20and%20light%20already%20existed.%20But%20there%20was%20no%20science%20of%20odor.%20Bell%20asked%20his%20readers%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmeasure%20a%20smell.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20smartphones%20in%20most%20people's%20pockets%20provide%20impressive%20built-in%20capabilities%20based%20on%20the%20sciences%20of%20sound%20and%20light%3A%20voice%20assistants%2C%20facial%20recognition%20and%20photo%20enhancement.%20The%20science%20of%20odor%20does%20not%20offer%20anything%20comparable.%20But%20that%20situation%20is%20changing%2C%20as%20advances%20in%20machine%20olfaction%2C%20also%20called%20%E2%80%9Cdigitized%20smell%2C%E2%80%9D%20are%20finally%20answering%20Bell's%20call%20to%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20on%20machine%20olfaction%20faces%20a%20formidable%20challenge%20due%20to%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20human%20sense%20of%20smell.%20Whereas%20human%20vision%20mainly%20relies%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fscience%2Fphotoreception%2FStructure-and-function-of-photoreceptors%5C%22%3Ereceptor%20cells%20in%20the%20retina%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20rods%20and%20three%20types%20of%20cones%20%E2%80%93%20smell%20is%20experienced%20through%20about%20400%20types%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fbody%2F23081-olfactory-nerve%5C%22%3Ereceptor%20cells%20in%20the%20nose%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMachine%20olfaction%20starts%20with%20sensors%20that%20detect%20and%20identify%20molecules%20in%20the%20air.%20These%20sensors%20serve%20the%20same%20purpose%20as%20the%20receptors%20in%20your%20nose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20to%20be%20useful%20to%20people%2C%20machine%20olfaction%20needs%20to%20go%20a%20step%20further.%20The%20system%20needs%20to%20know%20what%20a%20certain%20molecule%20or%20a%20set%20of%20molecules%20smells%20like%20to%20a%20human.%20For%20that%2C%20machine%20olfaction%20needs%20machine%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EApplying%20machine%20learning%20to%20smells%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMachine%20learning%2C%20and%20particularly%20a%20kind%20of%20machine%20learning%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mathworks.com%2Fdiscovery%2Fdeep-learning.html%5C%22%3Edeep%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20at%20the%20core%20of%20remarkable%20advances%20such%20as%20voice%20assistants%20and%20facial%20recognition%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMachine%20learning%20is%20also%20key%20to%20digitizing%20smells%20because%20it%20can%20learn%20to%20map%20the%20molecular%20structure%20of%20an%20odor-causing%20compound%20to%20textual%20odor%20descriptors.%20The%20machine%20learning%20model%20learns%20the%20words%20humans%20tend%20to%20use%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%2C%20%E2%80%9Csweet%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdessert%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20to%20describe%20what%20they%20experience%20when%20they%20encounter%20specific%20odor-causing%20compounds%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acs.org%2Fmolecule-of-the-week%2Farchive%2Fv%2Fvanillin.html%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DVanillin%252C%2520as%2520its%2520name%2520implies%2Calcohol%252C%2520aldehyde%252C%2520and%2520ether.%5C%22%3Evanillin%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20machine%20learning%20needs%20large%20datasets.%20The%20web%20has%20an%20unimaginably%20huge%20amount%20of%20audio%2C%20image%20and%20video%20content%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20train%20artificial%20intelligence%20systems%20that%20recognize%20sounds%20and%20pictures.%20But%20machine%20olfaction%20has%20long%20faced%20a%20data%20shortage%20problem%2C%20partly%20because%20most%20people%20cannot%20verbally%20describe%20smells%20as%20effortlessly%20and%20recognizably%20as%20they%20can%20describe%20sights%20and%20sounds.%20Without%20access%20to%20web-scale%20datasets%2C%20researchers%20weren't%20able%20to%20train%20really%20powerful%20machine%20learning%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20things%20started%20to%20change%20in%202015%20when%20researchers%20launched%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdream-olfaction.github.io%2F%5C%22%3EDREAM%20Olfaction%20Prediction%20Challenge%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20competition%20released%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1186%2Fs12868-016-0287-2%5C%22%3Edata%20collected%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fscholar%3Fhl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0%252C22%26q%3Dandreas%2Bkeller%2Bolfaction%26oq%3D%5C%22%3EAndreas%20Keller%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fhl%3Den%26user%3DDaB4TAEAAAAJ%26view_op%3Dlist_works%26sortby%3Dpubdate%5C%22%3ELeslie%20Vosshall%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20biologists%20who%20study%20olfaction%2C%20and%20invited%20teams%20from%20around%20the%20world%20to%20submit%20their%20machine%20learning%20models.%20The%20models%20had%20to%20predict%20odor%20labels%20like%20%E2%80%9Csweet%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9Cflower%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfruit%E2%80%9D%20for%20odor-causing%20compounds%20based%20on%20their%20molecular%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20performing%20models%20were%20published%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aal2014%5C%22%3Epaper%20in%20the%20journal%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017.%20A%20classic%20machine%20learning%20technique%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ibm.com%2Ftopics%2Frandom-forest%5C%22%3Erandom%20forest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20combines%20the%20output%20of%20multiple%20decision%20tree%20flow%20charts%2C%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20winner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fhl%3Den%26user%3Dttbl4FsAAAAJ%26view_op%3Dlist_works%26sortby%3Dpubdate%5C%22%3Emachine%20learning%20researcher%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20longstanding%20interest%20in%20applying%20machine%20learning%20to%20chemistry%20and%20psychiatry.%20The%20DREAM%20challenge%20piqued%20my%20interest.%20I%20also%20felt%20a%20personal%20connection%20to%20olfaction.%20My%20family%20traces%20its%20roots%20to%20the%20small%20town%20of%20Kannauj%20in%20northern%20India%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalgeographic.com%2Ftravel%2Farticle%2Fhow-did-kannauj-become-a-perfume-capital%5C%22%3EIndia's%20perfume%20capital%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Moreover%2C%20my%20father%20is%20a%20chemist%20who%20spent%20most%20of%20his%20career%20analyzing%20geological%20samples.%20Machine%20olfaction%20thus%20offered%20an%20irresistible%20opportunity%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20perfumery%2C%20culture%2C%20chemistry%20and%20machine%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProgress%20in%20machine%20olfaction%20started%20picking%20up%20steam%20after%20the%20DREAM%20challenge%20concluded.%20During%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20many%20cases%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinic.org%2Fsymptoms%2Floss-of-smell%2Fbasics%2Fdefinition%2Fsym-20050804%5C%22%3Esmell%20blindness%2C%20or%20anosmia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20were%20reported.%20The%20sense%20of%20smell%2C%20which%20usually%20takes%20a%20back%20seat%2C%20rose%20in%20public%20consciousness.%20Additionally%2C%20a%20research%20project%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpyrfume.org%2F%5C%22%3EPyrfume%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20made%20more%20and%20larger%20datasets%20publicly%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ESmelling%20deeply%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202019%2C%20the%20largest%20datasets%20had%20grown%20from%20less%20than%20500%20molecules%20in%20the%20DREAM%20challenge%20to%20about%205%2C000%20molecules.%20A%20Google%20Research%20team%20led%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fhl%3Den%26user%3DGPnusKcAAAAJ%26view_op%3Dlist_works%26sortby%3Dpubdate%5C%22%3EAlexander%20Wiltschko%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20finally%20able%20to%20bring%20the%20deep%20learning%20revolution%20to%20machine%20olfaction.%20Their%20model%2C%20based%20on%20a%20type%20of%20deep%20learning%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.nvidia.com%2Fblog%2Fwhat-are-graph-neural-networks%2F%5C%22%3Egraph%20neural%20networks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20established%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearch.google%2Fblog%2Flearning-to-smell-using-deep-learning-to-predict-the-olfactory-properties-of-molecules%2F%5C%22%3Estate-of-the-art%20results%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20machine%20olfaction.%20Wiltschko%20is%20now%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osmo.ai%2F%5C%22%3EOsmo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20mission%20is%20%E2%80%9Cgiving%20computers%20a%20sense%20of%20smell.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20Wiltschko%20and%20his%20team%20used%20a%20graph%20neural%20network%20to%20create%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1126%2Fscience.ade4401%5C%22%3Eprincipal%20odor%20map%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20where%20perceptually%20similar%20odors%20are%20placed%20closer%20to%20each%20other%20than%20dissimilar%20ones.%20This%20was%20not%20easy%3A%20Small%20changes%20in%20molecular%20structure%20can%20lead%20to%20large%20changes%20in%20olfactory%20perception.%20Conversely%2C%20two%20molecules%20with%20very%20different%20molecular%20structures%20can%20nonetheless%20smell%20almost%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20progress%20in%20cracking%20the%20code%20of%20smell%20is%20not%20only%20intellectually%20exciting%20but%20also%20has%20highly%20promising%20applications%2C%20including%20personalized%20perfumes%20and%20fragrances%2C%20better%20insect%20repellents%2C%20novel%20chemical%20sensors%2C%20early%20detection%20of%20disease%2C%20and%20more%20realistic%20augmented%20reality%20experiences.%20The%20future%20of%20machine%20olfaction%20looks%20bright.%20It%20also%20promises%20to%20smell%20good.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F221731%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthor%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fambuj-tewari-1505378%5C%22%3EAmbuj%20Tewari%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Statistics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-michigan-1290%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Michigan%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EDisclosure%20Statement%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fspan%3EAmbuj%20Tewari%20does%20not%20work%20for%2C%20consult%2C%20own%20shares%20in%20or%20receive%20funding%20from%20any%20company%20or%20organisation%20that%20would%20benefit%20from%20this%20article%2C%20and%20has%20disclosed%20no%20relevant%20affiliations%20beyond%20their%20academic%20appointment)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fai-is-cracking-a-hard-problem