%2F110609013.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ELast%20year%2C%20Malaika%20shared%20insights%20into%20her%20relationship%20and%20future%20plans%20with%20Arjun%20during%20an%20appearance%20at%20the%20India%20Today%20Conclave.%20She%20expressed%20that%20they're%20enjoying%20their%20current%20phase%20of%20love%2C%20referring%20to%20it%20as%20their%20%26quot%3Bpre-honeymoon%20phase%2C%26quot%3B%20indicating%20they're%20not%20in%20a%20rush%20to%20tie%20the%20knot%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Importance%20Of%20Your%20Belly%20Button%20And%20What%20It%20Reveals%20About%20Your%20Health%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENavels%2C%20belly%20buttons%2C%20innies%20or%20outies%20%E2%80%A6%20whatever%20term%20you%20use%2C%20your%20umbilicus%20may%20have%20plenty%20to%20tell%20you%20about%20the%20state%20of%20your%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20they%20are%20the%20thing%20of%20nightmares%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthline.com%2Fhealth%2Fomphalophobia%5C%22%3Eomphalophobia%3C%2Fa%3E%20(the%20fear%20of%20belly%20buttons)%20is%20a%20real%20condition.%20For%20others%2C%20they%20are%20a%20fashion%20accessory%20to%20be%20shown%20off%20in%20a%20crop%20top%2C%20or%20decorated%20with%20a%20body%20piercing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhatever%20your%20feelings%20about%20belly%20buttons%2C%20one%20thing's%20for%20sure%20-%20it%20once%20joined%20you%20to%20your%20mother.%20The%20umbilical%20cord%20is%20severed%20at%20birth%20to%20leave%20just%20a%20small%20clamped%20stump%20that%20progressively%20withers%20and%20falls%20away%20a%20week%20or%20two%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20you're%20left%20with%2C%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20is%20a%20small%20wrinkled%20depression.%20That's%20if%20you%20have%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinnie%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20most%20of%20us%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthline.com%2Fhealth%2Fbelly-button-types%5C%22%3E90%25%20apparently%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20do.%20From%20this%20point%2C%20the%20belly%20button%20seems%20to%20become%20redundant%20%E2%80%93%20other%20than%20to%20gather%20dust%20and%20fluff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20the%20whole%20story%20%E2%80%93%20your%20navel%20has%20more%20depth%20to%20it%20than%20just%20a%20few%20millimetres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20umbilicus%20is%20an%20access%20point%20for%20the%20vessels%20carrying%20blood%20to%20and%20from%20the%20foetus.%20These%20have%20come%20from%20the%20placenta%20and%20run%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kenhub.com%2Fen%2Flibrary%2Fanatomy%2Fumbilical-cord%5C%22%3Eumbilical%20cord%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20coated%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Ftopics%2Fmedicine-and-dentistry%2Fwharton-jelly%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DWharton%2520jelly%2520is%2520the%2520mucoid%2Ccord%2520perivascular%2520cells%2520(HUCPV).%5C%22%3EWharton's%20jelly%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20a%20gelatinous%20connective%20tissue%20contained%20in%20the%20cord%20that%20insulates%20and%20protects%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20normally%20three%20vessels%20within%20the%20cord.%20The%20one%20carrying%20oxygen%20and%20nutrients%20to%20the%20foetus%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F36785504%2F%5C%22%3Eumbilical%20vein%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20passes%20through%20the%20umbilicus%20and%20feeds%20into%20the%20developing%20foetal%20circulation.%20There%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.elsevier.com%2Fresources%2Fanatomy%2Fcardiovascular-system%2Farteries%2Fumbilical-artery%2F18563%5C%22%3Etwo%20umbilical%20arteries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20these%20carry%20deoxygenated%20blood%20and%20waste%20products%2C%20flowing%20in%20the%20other%20direction%20back%20to%20the%20placenta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FqCYosYUll3E%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20circulation%20is%20not%20needed%20after%20the%20baby%20is%20born%2C%20and%20once%20disconnected%20from%20the%20placenta%20the%20umbilical%20vessels%20naturally%20close%20up.%20But%20the%20little%20stump%20of%20cut%20cord%20left%20clinging%20on%20can%20still%20be%20of%20use%20for%20a%20short%20time%2C%20especially%20in%20newborn%20babies%20who%20are%20poorly.%20The%20vessels%20can%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8841780%2Fpdf%2Ffped-09-774705.pdf%5C%22%3Edrip%20lines%20inserted%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20be%20used%20for%20infusions%20of%20medicine%2C%20or%20have%20blood%20samples%20taken%20from%20them%20for%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20umbilicus%20is%20a%20portal%20in%20the%20wall%20of%20the%20abdomen%20-%20it's%20a%20little-known%20fact%20that%20during%20your%20embryonic%20development%20your%20intestines%20actually%20have%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembryology.med.unsw.edu.au%2Fembryology%2Findex.php%2FGastrointestinal_Tract_Development%5C%22%3Eleave%20your%20abdominal%20cavity%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20limited%20space%2C%20but%20return%20a%20few%20weeks%20later.%20They%20do%20so%20via%20the%20umbilicus%2C%20passing%20into%20the%20cord.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20the%20umbilicus%20is%20not%20just%20an%20access%20point%2C%20but%20a%20point%20of%20weakness.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhs.uk%2Fconditions%2Fumbilical-hernia-repair%2F%5C%22%3Eumbilical%20hernia%3C%2Fa%3E%20occurs%20if%20a%20section%20of%20intestine%20pokes%20through%20any%20gap.%20This%20may%20require%20an%20operation%20to%20correct%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20nun%20and%20the%20navel%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amjmedsci.org%2Farticle%2FS0002-9629(15)32023-1%2Fabstract%5C%22%3ESister%20Mary%20Joseph%20Dempsey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20was%20a%20nun%20who%20devoted%20much%20of%20her%20life%20to%20the%20care%20of%20patients%20in%20a%20hospital%20in%20Minnesota.%20She%20trained%20as%20a%20nurse%2C%20later%20becoming%20a%20surgical%20assistant%20to%20the%20doctor%20William%20Mayo.%20It%20was%20during%20this%20tenure%20that%20she%20highlighted%20an%20interesting%20observation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20(the%20late%2019th%20century)%2C%20cancers%20of%20the%20abdomen%20and%20pelvis%20were%20typically%20diagnosed%20much%20later%2C%20and%20unfortunately%20were%20often%20more%20extensive.%20We%20call%20this%20process%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cancer.net%2Fnavigating-cancer-care%2Fcancer-basics%2Fwhat-metastasis%5C%22%3Emetastasis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20a%20cancer%20starts%20in%20one%20organ%20or%20location%2C%20then%20spreads%20to%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%20Joseph%20noted%20that%20some%20patients%20with%20metastatic%20cancer%20had%20a%20new%20palpable%20swelling%20or%20nodule%20in%20their%20umbilicus.%20She%20did%20the%20noble%20deed%20of%20reporting%20this%20to%20Mayo%2C%20who%20fairly%20evidently%20hadn't%20noted%20it%20himself.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20rather%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1002%2Fca.23815%5C%22%3Eignominiously%20publish%20these%20findings%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20his%20own%20name%2C%20without%20giving%20due%20credit%20to%20his%20esteemed%20colleague.%20It%20was%20only%20after%20the%20deaths%20of%20Dempsey%20and%20Mayo%20-%20both%20in%201939%20-%20that%20another%20doctor%2C%20Hamilton%20Bailey%2C%20rightly%20named%20the%20finding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fomcr%2Farticle%2F2020%2F4-5%2Fomaa022%2F5842055%3Flogin%3Dfalse%5C%22%3ESister%20Mary%20Joseph's%20nodule%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FQSqEhClofgI%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdermnetnz.org%2Ftopics%2Fsister-mary-joseph-nodule-of-the-umbilicus%5C%22%3Enodule%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20firm%2C%20of%20variable%20colouring%2C%20and%20actually%20arises%20from%20spread%20of%20the%20cancer%20to%20the%20umbilical%20tissue.%20It's%20not%20seen%20as%20commonly%20these%20days%2C%20since%20more%20cancers%20are%20now%20diagnosed%20earlier%20before%20extensive%20spreading%20occurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EMedusa's%20head%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20signs%20can%20be%20observed%20in%20the%20navel%20that%20have%20a%20footing%20in%20mythology.%20One%20example%20allows%20us%20to%20draw%20a%20connection%20between%20the%20liver%20and%20the%20umbilicus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20skin%20around%20the%20navel%20has%20beds%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.elsevier.com%2Fresources%2Fanatomy%2Fcardiovascular-system%2Fveins%2Fparaumbilical-veins%2F22829%5C%22%3Esuperficial%20veins%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20feed%20back%20towards%20the%20deeper%20circulation.%20They%20actually%20drain%20blood%20into%20the%20hepatic%20portal%20vein%2C%20a%20large%20vessel%20that%20is%20heading%20into%20the%20liver%2C%20chock-full%20of%20nutrients%20absorbed%20from%20the%20gut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbritishlivertrust.org.uk%2Finformation-and-support%2Fliver-conditions%2Fportal-hypertension%2F%5C%22%3Epressure%20in%20the%20portal%20vein%20becomes%20too%20high%3C%2Fa%3E%20(mostly%20as%20a%20result%20of%20liver%20diseases%2C%20like%20alcohol%20cirrhosis)%20pressure%20builds%20in%20the%20connecting%20vessels%20too.%20Veins%20have%20thinner%20walls%20than%20arteries%20and%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7191313%2F%5C%22%3Eballoon%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20normally%20small%20veins%20around%20the%20navel%20dilate%20in%20size%20and%20become%20visible%20beneath%20the%20skin%2C%20fanning%20in%20all%20directions.%20This%20sign%2C%20like%20a%20head%20replete%20with%20snakes%20for%20hair%2C%20is%20named%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7191313%2F%5C%22%3Ecaput%20medusae%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20Medusa's%20head.%20In%20Greek%20mythology%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greekmythology.com%2FMyths%2FCreatures%2FMedusa%2Fmedusa.html%5C%22%3Ethe%20gorgon%20Medusa%3C%2Fa%3E%20whose%20head%20was%20severed%20by%20the%20hero%20Perseus%2C%20had%20the%20ability%20to%20turn%20anyone%20who%20beheld%20her%20gaze%20to%20stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20on%20that%20topic%2C%20all%20that%20dirt%2C%20debris%20and%20dead%20skin%20in%20our%20navels%20should%20also%20get%20an%20honourable%20(or%20maybe%20dishonourable)%20mention%20-%20prolonged%20accumulation%20of%20this%20material%20within%20the%20cavity%20can%20make%20it%20harden%20over%20time%2C%20forming%20a%20stony%20mass.%20We%20call%20this%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9552982%2F%5C%22%3Eomphalolith%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20umbilical%20stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FP08NIV0YkEU%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20umbilicus%20is%20something%20of%20a%20reliable%20crystal%20ball%20in%20diagnosing%20internal%20illnesses.%20But%20as%20to%20whether%20you%20regard%20it%20as%20an%20attractive%20part%20of%20your%20own%20anatomy%2C%20one%20has%20to%20ask%20the%20question%3A%20are%20you%20innie%20or%20outie%3F%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F228759%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3